==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Countercheck
<hw>Coun`ter*check"</hw> <pr>(koun`t?r-ch?k")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Counterchecked</conjf>
<pr>(-ch?ckt")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Counterchecking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To oppose or check by
some obstacle; to check by a return check.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Countercheck</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Countercheck
<hw>Coun"ter*check`</hw> <pr>(koun"t?r-ch?k`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A check; a stop; a rebuke, or censure to check a
reprover.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any force or device designed to restrain another
restraining force; a check upon a check.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The system of checks and <qex>counterchecks</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>J.
H. Newton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Counterclaim</ent>⟦br⟧
